{
  "stem": "4361.9",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that by his making it so worldwide, he does something to help put a nail in the coffin of the deniers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And for that, I wanted to thank him, and I did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this is what I want to say, that forgetting or trivializing the Holocaust is a sure mark, a sure sign of repeating it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I also want to say that comparing atrocities-- comparing the Gulag, comparing other atrocities, terrible atrocities-- to the Holocaust is wrong.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Holocaust was unique-- unique in its scope, unique in its genocide, genocidal power, force, evil, which was directed only against Jews.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "If all those six million Jews would have said, we convert, and we'll become rabid Nazis, it wouldn't have helped.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was a relentless extermination of Jews, and this is why the Holocaust is unique.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I am very pained when it is compared to anything else.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I would also like to my son, my hopefully grandchildren or anybody who listens to this tape, to understand the difference between a death camp and a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Jews were not slated for concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "A concentration camp was a picnic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Or if you consider that the Japanese were put in a concentration camp-- a terrible thing in this country-- and to say that I was in a concentration camp, it's a mockery.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It's a trivialization of the truth because a concentration camp in Nazi Germany-- and there were many concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I'm not saying there were none.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But being in a concentration camp was like being on the edge of the abyss, whereas being in something like Auschwitz, which was an extermination camp-- and so was Majdanek, Treblinka, et cetera, et cetera-- was being at the bottom of the abyss.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
